    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-07T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-07T09:00:00-05:00" n="287"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d287">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 033.5411/1</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SPA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-07T15:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 7, 1917, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 8, 8.20 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1012. The Minister for Foreign Affairs informs me that a special mission will
                    accompany Minister <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SH1">Sulzer</persName>
                    to the United States in order <pb facs="0414" n="1168" xml:id="pg_1168"/> to
                    explain the peculiar economic conditions of Switzerland in connection with the
                    possible restriction of foodstuff shipments from America. It will be composed of
                    Federal Councilor <persName>Syz</persName>, president of the Swiss Chamber of
                    Commerce; <persName>William Rappard</persName>, professor of political economy
                    in Genera and exchange professor of Harvard University; and Lieutenant Colonel
                        <persName>Staempfli</persName> of Berne, president of the Central Committee
                    for the Occupation of Internes.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
